Description: Fix CVE-2026-54301 - Same-Origin XSS in Respond to Webhook Node
 The Respond-to-Webhook binary-data and Buffer response branches did not
 emit the central Content-Security-Policy sandbox header that normal HTML
 responses use, allowing an authenticated workflow editor to serve a
 binary HTML payload that executes JavaScript in the n8n origin under
 another authenticated user's session (same-origin XSS).
 .
 Backport of upstream commit 3f7246b41a768a331efd7681a103cf30a293f725
 (release-candidate/2.25.x; released as n8n@2.25.7) onto target n8n@2.19.3.
 .
 The fix:
   1. Adds applySandboxCSP() helper in webhook-response-headers that sets
      `Content-Security-Policy: <sandbox>` on binary/buffer/streaming
      Respond-to-Webhook responses (unless sandboxing is explicitly
      disabled via env var).
   2. Calls applySandboxCSP() from both binary-data and Buffer response
      branches in setupResponseNodePromise() (webhook-helpers).
   3. Refactors webhook-request-handler to reuse applySandboxCSP().
 .
 The PROTECTED_HEADERS Set already exists in target 2.19.3 and already
 strips any user-supplied content-security-policy header, so no change
 is needed there.
Origin: backport, https://github.com/n8n-io/n8n/commit/3f7246b41a768a331efd7681a103cf30a293f725
Bug: https://github.com/n8n-io/n8n/security/advisories/GHSA-v733-mwr6-fgcm
Author: n8n upstream (cherry-picked from 71262655e46f2f78a4a15c58661226762f83365c)
